15
Subtitle
16
17 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING DISCLOSURE
18 FOR MATTERS REFERRED TO VOTERS; AND TO
19 BAN FOREIGN FUNDING FOR BALLOT MEASURES;
20 TO AMEND PORTIONS OF THE ARKANSAS CODE
21 THAT RESULTED FROM INITIATED ACT 1 OF
22 1996.
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
25
26 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative findings and intent.
27 The General Assembly finds that:
28 (1) It is vital to the operation of an effective democracy for
29 the people to have full and complete confidence in their elections;
30 (2) It is crucial that those elections be free of unwanted
31 foreign influence; and
32 (3) It is the intent of the General Assembly to prevent foreign
33 contributions from influencing the outcome of Arkansas elections.
34
35 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 7-6-201, concerning definitions for
36 campaign financing, resulting from Initiated Act 1 of 1996, is amended to add
